people_also_ask.question: Can I live in Hawaii on $2000 a month?
What products or services are produced in Hawaii?

value.text: Sugar cane and pineapples are Hawaii's most valuable crops. Hawaii also produces large quantities of flowers, much for export. Coffee, macadamia nuts, avocados, bananas, guavas, papayas, tomatoes and other fruits are grown.

people_also_ask.question: What's cheap to buy in Hawaii?
people_also_ask.answer_source: What foods are cheaper in Hawaii than on the mainland? - Quora

items.value: Tropical Fruits: Foods like pineapples, papayas, mangoes, and bananas can be less expensive in Hawaii since they are grown locally.
Fish and Seafood: Fresh fish, such as ahi (tuna) and other local seafood, can sometimes be cheaper due to proximity to the ocean and local fishing practices.

people_also_ask.question: Is $100,000 a good salary in Hawaii?

value.text: Making 100k is better than ``middle class'' if you're single. Definitely most people making 100k in Hawaii are not single. Hawaii is still expensive so it won't go that far, but I would say it's notably better than average for a single person.Dec 22, 2021
